WorkItem.Description:
Border style of text cells is ignored when generating a PDF from an Excel template in version 1.7.3c.
A Border is always drawn even if there is no border in the original Excel. 
Probably, this issue has to be corrected in PHPExcel\Shared\PDF\tcpdf.php.
Â 
It can be reproduced with the following code:
	include_once "PHPExcel/Reader/Excel5.php";
	$objReader = new PHPExcel_Reader_Excel5();
	$objPHPExcel  = $objReader->load('bordertest.xls');
	include_once 'PHPExcel/Writer/PDF.php';
	$objWriter = new PHPExcel_Writer_PDF($objPHPExcel);
	$objWriter->writeAllSheets();
	$objWriter->save('bordertest.pdf');
